					</li>
					<li>
						<label>Remington MCS</label>
						<canBeToggled>true</canBeToggled>
						<separateToggle>false</separateToggle>
						<description>Caliber: 12 Gauge. 3-round tube. Pump-action.
The Remington 870 MCS (Modular Combat System) Accessory Weapon is an ultra-compact, under-barrel shotgun configuration. Stripped of its stock and pistol grip, it mounts directly to the under-barrel rail of a host rifle. While functionally similar to the older KAC Masterkey, the MCS variant utilizes a modern quick-detach clamp that mounts seamlessly to standard Picatinny systems rather than proprietary barrel lugs. It provides infantrymen with rapid, integrated door-breaching capabilities without forcing them to swap weapons.</description>
